22 SECTION 1.(c) Appropriation. – There is appropriated from the General Fund to
23 the Office of State Fire Marshal in the Department of Insurance the sum of seven hundred fifty
24 thousand dollars ($750,000) nonrecurring for the 2025-2026 fiscal year to establish and
25 administer the Building Inspector Apprenticeship Program created by subsection (a) of this
26 section. These funds shall be used for program administration, coordination and provision of
27 training resources as described in G.S. 143-151.22(c), and the provision of local grant funds as
28 described in G.S. 143-151.22(d). The Department of Insurance shall include an evaluation of the
29 program's effectiveness, participation rates, impact on inspector availability, and
30 recommendations regarding future funding needs in its annual budget request submitted to the
31 Office of State Budget and Management and in any relevant reports to the Joint Legislative
32 Oversight Committee on General Government and the Fiscal Research Division.
33 SECTION 1.(d) Rulemaking. – The Code Officials Qualification Board, the Office
34 of State Fire Marshal, and the Department of Insurance may adopt rules necessary to implement
35 the provisions of this section.
36 SECTION 1.(e) Subsection (c) of this section becomes effective July 1, 2025. The
37 remainder of this section becomes effective October 1, 2025.
