19 collaborate with the North Carolina Licensing Board for General Contractors and relevant
20 construction industry associations. Their collaborative efforts shall promote awareness of the
21 Program and opportunities in Code enforcement among licensed general contractors.
22 (e) Rulemaking Authority. – The Board shall adopt rules necessary to implement the
23 provisions of this section. Such rules may cover specific eligibility criteria, application
24 procedures, standards for experience recognition, and requirements for successful program
25 completion.
26 (f) Integrity of Code Enforcement. – Nothing in this section shall be interpreted as
27 lowering the standards of competency required for Code-enforcement officials. Every Program
28 participant must meet the qualification standards set forth by the Board for the applicable level
29 of certification prior to independently performing Code enforcement duties requiring such
30 certification."
